Job Description
SALARY: $1800 - $2000
Duties &amp; Responsibilities:

  Perform routine maintenance of M&amp;E equipment.
  Maintain equipment checklist and recording of routine checks.
  Carry out work order requested by other departments.
  Attend to emergency, fire alarm, flooding and electrical failure.
  Check on Contractor's repair work and servicing.
  Standby after officer house for any breakdown of equipment.
  Carry out any other duties or instructions pertaining to the maintenance of the Lodge assigned by the Management.

Requirement:

  Minimum Nitec in Mechanical &amp; Electrical Services.
  Minimum 1 year working experience in electrical, plumbing and carpentry works and is familiar with tools and handyman matters.

Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.
